Autism Testing | Autism Evaluations | Soar Autism Center call Contact Us About Us About Us Our Approach Autism Testing Screening Our Team Get Started Family Resources Provider Resources Contact Us Acting early makes a difference Get Answers With Comprehensive Testing Do you have concerns or questions about how your young child is talking, learning, growing, or developing? Wondering if your child might benefit from testing for autism or other developmental conditions? Our child psychologist, Sarah Banks, PhD, brings multiple years of experience in assessing, testing, and evaluating young In addition, she prioritizes understanding where families are in their care journey and meeting them in that place with We are currently scheduling diagnostic tests for new clients at Soar Autism We accept most major insurances including Medicaid and typically have short wait times for young If you are interested in an assessment, call us at or click on “Schedule a Call” on the Get Started To learn more about Banks and the rest of our clinical team, including our speech therapist, occupational therapist, and board certified behavior analyst, read Our Team . Meet Banks Watch the video below of Sarah Banks and learn about her approach to autism testing, what a typical assessment is like at Soar, and her background as a child Take an Autism Test for My Child Are you wondering whether your child could have autism and want to take a screening test? Click here to take the , a screening tool intended for toddlers months of The stands for the Modified Checklist of Autism in Toddlers . It consists of a series of yes no questions that a parent or caregiver answers about their The is used on the Soar website with permission and copyrighted from Diana Robins, Deborah Fein, & Marianne FAQs Testing for Autism Overview of Autism Our Approach Family Resources Identification Testing for Autism Testing for autism How is autism tested for and diagnosed? It typically involves a test or assessment from a child psychologist or clinician who specializes in If you are concerned that your child may have autism or have been told by a healthcare professional to seek out an autism assessment, call us at Soar Autism Center at or ask your pediatrician for a How do I get my child evaluated or tested for autism? Typically a child psychologist or other clinician who specializes in autism testing and assessments can perform an We offer this service at Soar Autism Center with our psychologist Sarah We also have a list of other diagnostic providers in the greater Denver area for parents in our new parent kit . What happens at an autism assessment? Usually a standardized assessment or test is used in combination with a clinician’s independent During the assessment, the clinician will play with the child and watch for certain characteristics seen in children with Assessments should be fun, and a child shouldn’t know they are being The specific assessment used will vary depending on who evaluates your child, but examples of common assessments used in the US include the Autism Diagnostic Observation edition (ADOS-2), Autism Diagnostic (ADI-R), Childhood Autism Rating edition (CARS-2), and Gilliam Autism Rating Scale (GARS). How much does an autism test cost? Autism tests are typically covered by most health insurance plans, including The specific cost will vary based on the details of your health insurance plan (e.g. , deductibles). If you are wondering about the cost of an assessment with us, call us at and we can check your insurance benefits for I m not sure if my child needs an evaluation or not, what should I do? Call us at and talk to one of our intake specialists who can help assess if an evaluation with Banks is a good fit for your You can also talk to your pediatrician or other healthcare provider for their Is there an autism symptoms checklist or signs of autism checklist I can use with my child? Check out the signs of autism infographic that is on our Screening page . It shows different signs and symptoms of autism by age, as well as symptoms that can show at many different We also have videos of normal development from the What is the or F? The is also known as the Modified Checklist of Autism in It is a screening test used to identify children who may be at risk for autism, and is focused on toddlers (typically to months of age). It consists of a series of questions that the parent answers about their child and is often done at a visit with a It does not officially diagnose a child with autism but indicates possible risk of autism and that a diagnostic assessment may be beneficial for the You can take it online on our website here . My child had a high score, what do I do next? You should consult a healthcare provider, including your pediatrician and or a specialized provider who can evaluate for an autism We offer this service at Soar Autism Center, and we also have a list of other Colorado providers who perform diagnostic testing in our new parent

Announcing our new name: Streamlined About Log In Get started Announcing our new name: Streamlined March 4, After operating as Merchant Candy for a little over months,Â I m delighted to announce that Merchant Candy is now Streamlined . Back in , we embarked on a bold quest to transform B2B payments for the modern To get started, we met with businesses that were quickly expanding into wholesale and offered to deal with the paper checks and unintelligible Realizing just how unpleasant the payment experience was, we decided to focus on making invoice payments even The name Merchant Candy drew us to be creative in our approach and delightful in our It pushed us to think of ways in which we could help our customers thrive, and it inspired us to focus on two particularly acute problems in B2BÂ payments - 1)Â Accepting any form of payment from a Payor, even if it s a paper 2)Â Matching those payments back to the invoices, so our customers didn t have Over the last few months, we ve made incredible strides in both these We ve built a payment processor from the ground up to offer an unrivaled payment experience for both parties in a B2BÂ Today, Payors have the ultimate flexibility to pay using a payment method that works for them, while payees always get paid faster We process tens of thousands of payments on behalf of our customers and automatically reconcile those payments back to invoices - saving team on average hours week. Weâve grown tremendously thanks to the trust placed in us by our early merchant Not only that, but weâre incredibly proud of how far weâve come in such as short time span, but we also recognize that we have so much more to do to power the $25 trillion B2B payment Updating our name to Streamlined better aligns us as a company with our prime objective, using only a single We aim to help businesses streamline invoicing and payments, so they can focus on Naming aside, our product, vision and commitment to the future and the transformation of B2BÂ payments remain the same today as it was when we started, only with a new name serving as a north If you d like to learn more about Streamlined and how it could help you, feel free to grab a demo . Where it all began Our Story Since , the American Land Title Association (ALTA) has explored what makes the title industry special as well as a great opportunity for We talked with ALTA members about the common values that run through the fabric of all title The ALTA Our Values initiative helped identify the industry’s true north stars of We Lead, We Deliver and We Building off that, we began the Tell Our Story campaign to publicly celebrate the diverse and wonderful stories of title professionals and the good they do in their ALTA members long have been active in their neighborhoods, not only protecting American homebuyers, but also supporting local charitable During the pandemic in , we saw title professionals across the United States stepping up to help their neighbors, customers and local As we shared these efforts through the next step in our evolution, the #GoodDeeds campaign, it became clear that ALTA can be a force multiplier, amplifying our members’ efforts and their Therefore, was a natural time to establish a new charitable foundation dedicated to empowering our members to help their The ALTA Good Deeds Foundation provides charitable grants to (c)(3) organizations supported by ALTA Grants are awarded to local organizations through a competitive application process completed by an ALTA member, highlighting how the member is furthering Our Values through charitable Want to get involved? Home About Us News and Updates Contact Home About Us News and Updates Contact Delivering Inside A Signal Propagation Problem promises to bring bandwidth speeds up to times faster than with much lower However, the frequencies used to enable these higher speeds lead to a reduction in how far the signal can Up to technologies, cellular networks have used spectrum bands that range from MHz to Now with the introduction of , additional spectrum bands have been introduced that range from sub 6 GHz to between and (mmWave). Carriers are counting on mmWave to deliver extremely high data rates, but physics dictates that the higher the frequency the shorter the range of the This problem is only amplified when the signal must propagate through For signals to penetrate buildings they must overcome many different types of materials such as glass, wood, concrete, There are several studies that attempt to quantify the loss associated with building materials, but the bottom line is that higher frequency signals have a higher loss through all types of building Going Around the Barriers to Communication PHYTunes has found an alternative mechanism to deliver cellular signals around Cellular Subscriber Lines (CSL) is the leading technology innovation that addresses coverage and deployment cost As shown in the diagram above CSL deploys the novel concept of using existing infrastructure such as telephone lines, cables, ethernet wires, and coaxial cables in conjunction with the wireless infrastructure to quickly and inexpensively extend the coverage of signals inside homes and PHYTunes is developing two product families for deployment the CSL IF which attaches to the BBU and the CSL RF which is a very “tuner” which will be inside the building and broadcast a With CSL, PHYTunes intends to accelerate the deployment of and quickly enable commercial and private subscribers to reap the benefits of this exciting I’m happy to be PhyTunes Chair and am excited about PhyTunes technological innovation to drive much lower deployment cost, lower power, and lower latency into homes and buildings John Cioffi, The Interpres Security platform offers a customized, continuous, and analysis of an organization’s detection and mitigation capabilities and provides automated security engineering directives based on this evaluation, ultimately enabling a hardened security posture in the most efficient manner To address the expanding number of cybersecurity threats, organizations now use an average of tools in their security stack . Despite this level of investment, organizations still do not know how effective this tooling is against their specific and expanding threat Without a clear picture of the most relevant threats or how well their current tools work against them, organizations do not have a complete view of how they After experiencing a systems breach firsthand at a classified security operations center, members of the Interpres Security founding team developed a new Threat Centric Methodology to validate the effectiveness of all of the security vendors in the This approach proved successful, and later the same methodology became the genesis for Interpres Security’s automation of these capabilities into their new Interpres Security currently integrates the MITRE ATT&CK framework to prioritize threat coverage based on the adversaries most likely to target an organization, the malware and techniques those adversaries use, and the prevalence of those attacks as seen in the It then recommends mitigations, telemetry collection strategies, and detection logic best suited to fill the prioritized gaps in coverage across the enterprise to detect and mitigate threats most likely to target the It does all this while utilizing the organization’s existing investment in cybersecurity products and Once the defense ecosystem is optimized, Interpres maintains this state through a situational awareness dashboard that detects drift in configuration and changes to risk posture while offering detailed “Until now, only large security engineering teams have even been able to attempt to analyze, validate, and optimize an organization’s specific security toolset and However, the detailed analysis and threat intelligence needed is extremely and manually intensive to The capabilities that we have automated within the Interpres platform goes beyond the scope of what humans can complete regularly, in ,” said Nick Lantuh, Chief Executive Officer and at Interpres Security and former Founder and President of NetWitness (acquired by EMC in ). “It’s time for a new Automation and prioritization are necessary to properly assess, configure, optimize and align current security tools to optimally defend against advanced threats in a timely That’s the value of the Intepres ” “We see CISOs regularly struggle to get a handle on which security tools are most effective for their organization’s specific needs,” said Mark Hatfield, General Partner at Ten Eleven Ventures and new board member at Interpres “They want to hold the vendors accountable for what they’ve promised – to understand how well their tools stand up to threats they are most likely to The exceptional team at Interpres Security has developed a platform that does exactly that – help companies ‘shrink the stack’, get the most out of their existing cybersecurity investments, understand where they are and are not protected, rationalize product investments and harden their ” About Interpres Security Interpres Security makes security performance intelligible and provable for the enterprise with a comprehensive new approach to managing the defense With Interpres, security teams can take a perspective to understand what their current tools can detect and defend against, identify gaps and inefficiencies, and iteratively improve their security posture with a and custom tailored Interpres Security is backed by top cybersecurity specialist investor, Ten Eleven To learn more, request a demonstration of the platform and follow the company on LinkedIn or Twitter . Privacy Policy - Branch Energy Branch Energy Holdings Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is collected, used, and shared when you visit or make a purchase from (the “Site”). PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECT When you visit the Site, we automatically collect certain information about your device, including information about your web browser, IP address, time zone, and some of the cookies that are installed on your Additionally, as you browse the Site, we collect information about the individual web pages or products that you view, what websites or search terms referred you to the Site, and information about how you interact with the We refer to this information as “Device ” We collect Device Information using the following technologies: – “Cookies” are data files that are placed on your device or computer and often include an anonymous unique For more information about cookies, and how to disable cookies, visit http: www.allaboutcookies.org. – “Log files” track actions occurring on the Site, and collect data including your IP address, browser type, Internet service provider, referring exit pages, and date time – “Web beacons,” “tags,” and “pixels” are electronic files used to record information about how you browse the Additionally when you make a purchase or attempt to make a purchase through the Site, we collect certain information from you, including your name, billing address, shipping address, payment information (including credit card numbers), email address, and phone We refer to this information as “Order ” When we talk about “Personal Information” in this Privacy Policy, we are talking both about Device Information and Order HOW DO WE USE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION? We use the Order Information that we collect generally to fulfill any orders placed through the Site (including processing your payment information, arranging for shipping, and providing you with invoices and or order confirmations). Additionally, we use this Order Information to: Communicate with you Screen our orders for potential risk or fraud and When in line with the preferences you have shared with us, provide you with information or advertising relating to our products or We use the Device Information that we collect to help us screen for potential risk and fraud (in particular, your IP address), and more generally to improve and optimize our Site (for example, by generating analytics about how our customers browse and interact with the Site, and to assess the success of our marketing and advertising campaigns). SHARING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION We share your Personal Information with third parties to help us use your Personal Information, as described For example, we use Shopify to power our online store–you can read more about how Shopify uses your Personal Information here: https: www.shopify.com legal privacy. We also use Google Analytics to help us understand how our customers use the Site–you can read more about how Google uses your Personal Information here: https: www.google.com intl en policies privacy . You can also of Google Analytics here: https: tools.google.com dlpage gaoptout. Finally, we may also share your Personal Information to comply with applicable laws and regulations, to respond to a subpoena, search warrant or other lawful request for information we receive, or to otherwise protect our DO NOT TRACK Please note that we do not alter our Site’s data collection and use practices when we see a Do Not Track signal from your YOUR RIGHTS If you are a European resident, you have the right to access personal information we hold about you and to ask that your personal information be corrected, updated, or If you would like to exercise this right, please contact us through the contact information DATA RETENTION When you place an order through the Site, we will maintain your Order Information for our records unless and until you ask us to delete this CHANGES We may update this privacy policy from time to time in order to reflect, for example, changes to our practices or for other operational, legal or regulatory CONTACT US For more information about our privacy practices, if you have questions, or if you would like to make a complaint, please contact us by at [email protected] or by mail using the details provided below: For more information: [email protected] 1 (844) Privacy Policy   Email Protection | Cloudflare Please enable Email Protection You are unable to access this email address The website from which you got to this page is protected by Email addresses on that page have been hidden in order to keep them from being accessed by malicious You must enable Javascript in your browser in order to decode the address . 5 Hidden Mistakes That are Hurting Your Demo Sales 5 Hidden Mistakes That are Hurting Your Demo Sales Solutions Use Cases Integrations Get early access September , 5 Hidden Mistakes That are Hurting Your Demo Sales SHARE SHARE TWEET Are you struggling with converting your demos into sales? If so youâre not Plenty of companies have a hard time with their rate, and each could be suffering from a different problem thatâs hindering their Think about whatâs keeping your Is it the competitive landscape? Are you repeatedly pitching to unqualified leads? Has wreaked its havoc on your business? All of these reasons, as well as high sales turnover, are all solid reasons as to why youâre not seeing any But in reality, these issues are not directly influencing your demo When we think about the demo conversion rate, we should first and foremost think about what is influencing our demosÂ and what we can do to deliver To help sales teams do so, we wanted to highlight the most common mistakes remote sales teams make during the process and provide new approaches to solve these In this post weâll explore the following five mistakes:Â Lack of product and demo knowledgeÂ Failing to adjust the demo to customerâs needs ..Â at scale Neglecting to validate the value using relevant information Relying on the wrong data to gain visibility into the sales demo processÂ Ignoring demo best practices (there are many of them)Â Lack of Product and Demo Knowledge Based on our teamâs years of experience and dozens of interviews we conducted with leading software companies, we realised that in most companies information is distributed across many different roles and Which in turns means companies create an elaborate onboarding plan, in which new sales representatives sit in dozens of meetings and countless training activities with each department to learn as much as they can until they are pronounced Imagine yourself in your new employeesâ shoes, going through this process and attempting to learn a whole new product, product value proposition and sales Itâs a lot of information, and the method itself isnât incredibly People are likely to forget more than percent of what they learned after only a month! Meaning everything theyâve crammed into their brains during the onboarding process will quickly As managers you can continue fighting the forgetting curve , or you can start looking into emerging remote sales tools that utilize learning Failing to adjust the demo to customerâs needs at scaleÂ A great sales rep understands that a good sales pitch is about the customers and the value rather than about the company or specific So how can you help your team focus on the customer without decreasing sales effectiveness?Â A common mistake most sales managers make is spending a considerable amount of time training new employees on the entire product and asking them to build the demo You wonât let your BDR wing it on every outbound call, so why would you do that with your sales reps? Implementing a sales playbook yields better Itâs best to think of a suggested demo flow that includes a unique product click path and talk track that emphasises a specific set of Â But wonât a playbook conflict with the repâs ability to adjust the demo to the customer? On the contrary, the best sales teams build their demos according to one or more of the following elements: persona, industry, use case and company This allows your reps to immediately adapt to every customer and it is much easier to gain control and to react to customerâs needs when you already have a good value hypothesis in Finally, working with a playbook helps new reps shift their pitch from a product focus to value focus and - for more experienced reps - to break their demo Neglecting to Validate the Value Using Relevant Information Did you know that people are percent more likely to believe you if you use numbers?Â This isnât true, but Iâm guessing you found the statement more reliable because of the Using proven data and statistics is key in remote When I began my career, I was on delivering value during my demos, always answering the question: âwhy should you care about our product?â At a certain point I realized my next jump in sales wouldnât come by improving this particular aspect of my I began researching the psychology behind the sales and quickly understood that one of the principles of persuasion is When you add relevant customer stories, statistics, industry news, and ROI benchmarks to your pitch, you gain credibility and encourage your customer to take this huge leap of faith and purchase your This is not necessarily the most important part of your sales demo, but in many cases it is the most neglected part of sales Relying on the wrong data to gain visibility into the sales demo processÂ Â As a sales manager you collect information about every aspect of the sales process: prospecting, qualification, negotiation and so But do you have data that pro

Anxiety can latch on to a wide range of situations including dealing with stress at work, taking a test, handling relationships, going on dates, even hanging out with In addition to psychological symptoms, it is common for sufferers to feel physical Common psychological symptoms include: Feeling persistently worried and afraid about everyday interactions Constantly overthinking plans and responsibilities Having difficulty making decisions on your own Having trouble falling asleep or staying asleep Struggling to concentrate or complete work Being unable to relax and enjoy activities Obsessing over “worst case scenarios” Having an intense fear of failure Being unable to “let things go” Feeling “on edge” Common physical symptoms include: Fatigue Nausea Stomach pain Shortness of breath Shaking or tremors Increased heart rate Excessive perspiration Muscle aches or tension Nervousness and irritability Rapid breathing (hyperventilation) What causes anxiety? Anxiety can manifest from a combination of environmental and biological In some cases, past trauma can also be a contributing How is it treated? A mental health professional can treat anxiety with any combination of therapy, medication, and lifestyle The most common form of therapy to treat anxiety is Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT). In CBT, a therapist will help you identify what triggers your symptoms, challenge and replace negative thinking patterns, and adopt more constructive These tools will be instrumental in helping you make progress, manage, and engage your Depression | Trauma & PTSD | OCD | Relationship Issues | Grief & Loss | Chronic Illness | Substance Abuse | Borderline Personality Ready to find your group? Phexxi is a new form of birth control, called a vaginal pH It comes in the form of a vaginal gel, and you use it right before It is effective immediately and lasts for an Phexxi is meant to be used “on demand” and only when you need it, but it is important to note that it is not effective if used after One of the top questions we get is ” How Effective is Phexxi ?” Great question! We are happy to report it is to % effective on its Phexxi may also be used with condoms made with latex, polyurethane, or polyisoprene, and vaginal diaphragms for increased How it works You submit a minute questionnaire and from there we will review your medical history and preferences within hours (M-F 9 :30pm PST) We will review your medical history, and a provider will check in with you via text to confirm If no additional steps are required, medications can be picked up at your local pharmacy or will be shipped by our partner pharmacy, and the Choix team will be on hand to help you along the We can then have contraception delivered through our partner pharmacy or you can pick it up at your local pharmacy – whatever is most convenient for Cost $15 Consultation fee + cost for Please note that the cost for contraception depends on the pharmacy you use and whether or not you use Requirements You are years of age and in the states of California, Colorado, Illinois, Maine, New Mexico or Take the Questionnaire I’d like to work with What’s next? You will need: Height and weight measurements Photo ID and a clear selfie for purposes of identification Payment information Once we receive your information, we’ll be in touch within ! CoverRight is dedicated to delivering an enrollment experience from research, evaluation to You can think of us as your free personal Medicare concierge Our goal is to be the only insurance site you need for enrolling in That means we: Offer all the top insurance companies so you don’t have to shop elsewhere Explain what you need to know in plain English so you don’t have to research elsewhere There is no “one size fits all” Medicare solution and a plan may seem less expensive up front but end up costing you more in the long At CoverRight, we partner with you to remove the guesswork so you have complete clarity and We combine research tools with knowledge of the Medicare to find you the coverage that best fits your individual You can connect with licensed insurance agent that can answer your questions and walk through the best options based on your personal healthcare and Is your service free? Yes, CoverRight’s services are % free and there is no obligation whatsoever to enroll in a At CoverRight, we are committed to independent advice and our agents are dedicated to providing unbiased insurance We will not try to upsell or steer you into a plan that does not suit your How does CoverRight make money? As a company, we get paid a commission by insurance companies for enrolling you in an insurance But don’t worry: these commissions do not impact the price you receive or are quoted for different Medicare plans whether you purchase them through us or directly with an insurance This means you never pay extra to use our We understand that commissions introduce a potential conflict of But we avoid that conflict by: Being transparent: we show you all quotes from a wide panel of insurance companies, so that you have full clarity on your options Focusing on advice: we publish free resources to help you make smart decisions about health Our licensed experts also focus on advice and customer service, not Being : one of our company values is to do the right thing for our We are committed to never upselling or steering you into a plan that does not suit your needs and will happily let you know if your current plan is the best plan for your Is it more expensive to buy insurance through CoverRight? No, whether you enroll into a Medicare health insurance plan with us, with another agent broker or directly from Insurance Company X, you cannot get a cheaper price for the same policy from Insurance Company This is because each insurance company files their prices with the federal regulator, and everyone has to use those It is illegal for us or anyone else to discount that However, you can save money and make smart decisions by comparing insurance policies across the market (like Amazon) . Each company competes to offer you the best coverage and you as a consumer At CoverRight, we strive to offer all the top insurance companies, to make sure you get the best policy for you and save Is CoverRight affiliated with any Insurance Carriers? No, CoverRight is an independent insurance What that means is that we represent multiple insurance companies and have no bias to recommend one over We work with over insurance companies across the country so you can be confident that you’re buying from a very reputable insurance company, and getting the best For us it’s important you find the right insurance policy for your When insurance companies compete for your business, you What types of health insurance do you sell? BAKX Therapeutics is coming soon   Learn About What Is In Our Pipeline | Bakx Therapeutics Science Platform Pipeline Team Publications Contact Search Menu Menu Pipeline Program Discovery Preclinical Phase 1 Phase 2 Phase 3 BKX – BAX (Leukemia Lymphoma) (Solid Tumors) BKX is an oral small molecule activator of the associated X (Bax). BKX binds to the trigger site of BAX in a catalytic manner, stimulating a conformational change in Bax to drive apoptosis in tumor cells BKX is active in heme malignancies including AML, DLBCL & CLL combinations with venetoclax (or other family inhibitors)- in vitro and in vivo studies have shown synergistic effect providing an approach for treating resistant tumors combo is also currently being evaluated for rational combination approaches with other agents for solid tumors BKX – Undisclosed target (Solid Tumors) BKX is a discovery program focused on a family protein very strongly expressed in multiple solid tumors & hematological The BAKX approach targets the unique interactions of the target with other members of the family to overcome the historical challenges associated with drugging the This is enabled by the use of computational methods such as ‘swimming simulations’ to target interactions that would be challenging to elucidate with traditional structural biology BKX – Undisclosed target (Solid Tumors) BKX is an early stage discovery program focused on a family protein which has not been previously targeted from a therapeutic BAKX unique knowledge of this protein and computational simulation capabilities allow us to pursue this novel target Who We Are We are cancer biologists, clinicians, and researchers passionate about making better Quick Links Science Platform Pipeline Team Publications Contact Follow Us Contact Information For information about partnering, investing & [email protected] © Copyright - BAKX All Rights Website Design by Tomo360 .
